orrectOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ebuccinator\u003C/strong\u003E muscle is supplied by the facial nerve (CN VII). It is one of the muscles of facial expression, which are all innervated by the facial nerve.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other muscles listed are involved in mastication and are innervated by the mandibular branch of the trigeminal nerve (CN V):\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETemporalis\u003C/strong\u003E - innervated by the mandibular branch of the trigeminal nerve\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELateral pterygoid\u003C/strong\u003E - innervated by the mandibular branch of the trigeminal nerve\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMedial pterygoid\u003C/strong\u003E - innervated by the mandibular branch of the trigeminal nerve\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMasseter\u003C/strong\u003E - innervated by the mandibular branch of the trigeminal nerve\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The facial nerve (CN VII) innervates the muscles of facial expression, including the buccinator muscle.","The muscles of mastication, such as temporalis, masseter, and the pterygoids, are innervated by the mandibular branch of the trigeminal nerve (CN V)."],"references":["Singh, V. (2023). Textbook of Anatomy-Head, Neck and Brain, Volume III-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Patestas, M. A., \u0026 Gartner, L. P. (2016). A textbook of neuroanatomy. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Patel, C. R., Fernandez-Miranda, J. C., Wang, W. H., \u0026 Wang, E. W. (2016). Skull Base Anatomy. Otolaryngologic clinics of North America, 49(1), 9\u201320. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.otc.2015.09.001","Anderson, B. W., Kortz, M. W., Black, A. C., \u0026 Al Kharazi, K. A. (2023). Anatomy, Head and Neck, Skull. In StatPearls. StatPearls Publishing"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58750"}},"ques